<p>Houston's hot-humid climate demands robust HVAC systems designed specifically for extended cooling seasons and high humidity management. The ideal HVAC system for Houston homes should feature a minimum SEER rating of 16, with SEER 18-20 systems providing optimal efficiency for the climate. Central air conditioning with variable-speed compressors performs exceptionally well, as these systems can adjust output to match cooling demands while maintaining consistent humidity control.</p>

