<p>Houston residents benefit from multiple layers of solar and HVAC incentives that significantly reduce installation costs. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit for solar installations through 2032, stepping down to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. This credit applies to the total system cost, including equipment, installation, and permits, making it the most valuable incentive available to Houston homeowners.</p>

<p>While Texas doesn't offer state-level solar rebates, the absence of state income tax means Houston residents keep more of their solar savings. CenterPoint Energy offers net metering programs that credit excess solar production at retail rates, though recent policy changes have modified these arrangements. Property tax exemptions for solar installations mean the added home value from solar doesn't increase property taxes. Additionally, HVAC system upgrades may qualify for federal tax credits when they meet specific efficiency requirements, with high-efficiency heat pumps and central air systems eligible for credits up to \$2,000.</p>

