<p>Houston's diverse neighborhoods each present unique considerations for solar and HVAC installations. The Heights and Montrose areas feature many historic homes with mature tree canopies that may require careful solar panel positioning to avoid shading while preserving the neighborhood's character. These areas often need updated electrical panels to accommodate modern solar systems.</p>

<p>Energy Corridor and Katy area homes, typically built in recent decades, offer ideal conditions for solar installations with newer electrical systems and optimal roof orientations. These neighborhoods' larger lot sizes and 2,500+ square foot homes often justify 8-10kW solar systems. Memorial and River Oaks areas feature luxury homes requiring high-capacity HVAC systems and premium solar solutions that maintain aesthetic appeal while maximizing performance. Sugar Land and Pearland suburban areas provide excellent solar potential with minimal shading and modern construction that easily accommodates both solar and high-efficiency HVAC systems.</p>

